# Coding Standards

## TypeScript
- Strict mode; no `any` — use `unknown` with type guards
- Interface for object shapes; no enums — use `as const`
- Explicit return types on exported functions

## Imports
```typescript
// 1. React/Next → 2. Third-party → 3. @/ internal → 4. Relative
import type { Metadata } from 'next';
import { motion } from 'framer-motion';
import { Container } from '@/components/layout/Container';
import { ServiceCard } from './ServiceCard';
```

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`ServiceCard.tsx`)
- Hooks: `use{Name}.ts`
- Utilities/queries: kebab-case (`get-all-services.ts`)
- Constants: SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE

## Quality
- Max 200 lines per file
- No commented-out code
- No `console.log` in production
- Run `npm run lint` and `npm run build` before completing
